Client Service Leaders
 

Heidi L. Amspaugh
Principal, Indianapolis, IN


Contact Information 
(317) 465-1517 amspaugh@umbaugh.com 



Heidi Amspaugh joined Umbaugh as an Analyst in 2006 after working as an intern. She graduated from Indiana University - Bloomington with a Bachelor of Science degree in Public Affairs from the School of Public and Environmental Affairs (SPEA) with a concentration in Public Financial Management, and with a certificate in Non-Profit Management. She is a registered Municipal Advisor and holds a Certified Independent Professional Municipal Advisor (CIPMA) designation.
Heidi has been involved in many areas of the firm’s practice, including economic development, tax increment finance (TIF), structuring incentive packages for industrial/commercial prospects, and the financial planning associated with the issuance of both tax-exempt and taxable bonds for communities around the State.
Heidi has been on various panels discussing public financial management topics for the School of Public and Environmental Affairs at Indiana University – Bloomington and for many Indiana associations. She serves on the Board of the National Association of Municipal Advisors (NAMA) and was recently elected as Treasurer for Indiana Economic Development Association (IEDA).
Back to top 




 

Doug L. Baldessari, CPA
Partner, Indianapolis, IN


Contact Information 
(317) 465-1508 baldessari@umbaugh.com 



Doug Baldessari’s practice includes financial studies and projects for municipally-owned water, sewage and stormwater utilities, not-for-profit water, regional water and sewer districts and conservancy districts. These projects often involve bond financing, financial analysis and determining utility revenue requirements, cost-of-service studies and financial planning associated with capital acquisition.
He has served as an expert accounting witness before the Indiana Utility Regulatory Commission on behalf of clients in connection with improvement projects, bond issues, and rate increases. He has been a guest speaker for various professional organizations.
Baldessari has been with Umbaugh since 2000 and is based in the Indianapolis office. He is a member of the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants, the Indiana CPA Society and the American Water Works Association.
Baldessari received his Master of Professional Accountancy from Indiana University and is a graduate of the University of Connecticut with a degree in business with a concentration in finance.
Back to top 




 

Brian C. Colton
Partner, Indianapolis, IN


Contact Information 
(317) 465-1516 colton@umbaugh.com 



Brian C. Colton leads the Public Finance Group and serves on the management committee of Umbaugh. Brian’s practice includes tax increment financing, economic development, municipal bond issues, capital project planning, property tax appeal issues and annexation fiscal plans. Colton has been involved in a number of special projects at Umbaugh, including: the creation of the firm’s right-of-way user fees report for the Indiana Association of Cities and Towns, assisting with fiscal home rule reports for the Accelerate Indiana Municipalities and the Association of Indiana Counties and assisting with the firm’s analysis of the estimated impact of recent and proposed property tax regulations on TIF areas throughout Indiana.
Colton has been a guest lecturer on local government finance topics for the School of Public and Environmental Affairs at Indiana University – Bloomington, on local government funding for the Association of Indiana Counties, on public-private partnerships for the Indiana Association of Cities and Towns Municipal Management Institute and on SEC Regulations for the National Association of Municipal Advisors.
Colton joined Umbaugh in 1997. He has a degree in economics and political science from the University of Iowa and a Master of Public Affairs with concentrations in public financial management and policy analysis from the School of Public and Environmental Affairs at Indiana University. Colton is based in Umbaugh’s Indianapolis office.
Back to top 




 

Brian S. Cooper
Principal, Columbus, OH


Contact Information 
614-987-1681 cooper@umbaugh.com 



Brian Cooper concentrates on general obligation, income tax revenue, non-tax revenue and special revenue bonds. Since 2003, Cooper has worked on 120 distinct project financings in Ohio representing over $2.75 billion in financed projects for municipal finance, economic development, utilities and infrastructure.
Cooper graduated from the Ohio State University in 2001 and is a municipal advisor registered with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC) and with the Municipal Securities Rulemaking Board (MSRB).
He has been a presenter at the Council of Development Finance Agencies’ national conference and serves as their muni bond advisor for both beginner and advanced bond courses and has also presented at the annual conferences for the Ohio Economic Development Association, the Ohio Government Finance Officers Association and is a guest lecturer at the Ohio State University.
Cooper joined Umbaugh in 2015 when his practice, ACI Advisors, LLC, merged with Umbaugh. He is based in Umbaugh’s Columbus, Ohio office.
Back to top 




 

Christina Cromer, CPA
Principal, Indianapolis, IN


Contact Information 
(317) 465-1518 cromer@umbaugh.com 



Christina Cromer’s practice focuses on arbitrage rebate which helps issuers of tax-exempt debt navigate the complexities of the IRS Code and Regulations. She assists clients in identifying exceptions to rebate for which they may qualify, and when necessary, prepares rebate liability and yield reduction payment calculations.
Christina has been with Umbaugh since 2006. She is a honor graduate from the Kelly School of Business at Indiana University in Indianapolis with Bachelor of Science degrees in both Accounting and Finance. She is a member of the Indiana CPA Society and the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants. She resides in Greenwood and is based in Umbaugh’s Indianapolis office.
Back to top 




 

Christina M. De Witt, CPA
Principal, Indianapolis, IN


Contact Information 
(317) 465-1525 dewitt@umbaugh.com 



Christina M. De Witt has been involved in financial studies for municipally-owned utilities, rate filings with the Indiana Utility Regulatory Commission, not-for-profit corporations, regional water and sewer districts and conservancy districts. These studies quite often have involved the determination of utility revenue requirements, cost of service studies and the financial planning associated with the issuance of tax-exempt bonds.
She is a licensed Certified Public Accountant in the state of Indiana and is a member of the Indiana CPA Society, the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants, and the American Water Works Association.
De Witt is a graduate of Franklin College with a degree in Bachelor of Science Degree in Accounting. Christina joined Umbaugh in March of 2005.
De Witt lives in Indianapolis and is based in Umbaugh’s Indianapolis office.
Back to top 




 

Matthew R. Eckerle
Principal, Indianapolis, IN


Contact Information 
(317) 465-1520 eckerle@umbaugh.com 



Matt Eckerle is a Principal at Umbaugh, and he has been with the firm as a full-time staff member since June 2005.  He graduated from Indiana University - Bloomington in May 2005 with a B.S. in Business with a Finance concentration from the Kelley School of Business.  Matt spent two summers prior to his graduation from Indiana as an intern at Umbaugh.
Matt has been involved in many areas of the firm’s practice including public infrastructure financing and economic development financing for communities around the State of Indiana.   Matt has assisted communities around Indiana with the preparation and negotiation of economic development incentives, evaluation of and planning for tax increment financing (TIF) areas, annual reporting requirements, capital projects financings, and the development or update of recreation impact fees.  Matt has assisted in preparing special legislative analyses for Accelerate Indiana Municipalities and the Indiana Economic Development Association, and he has participated as a guest speaker at conferences of various Indiana local government and economic development associations and as a panelist at an annual conference of the National Association of Municipal Advisors. Matt is a Certified Independent Professional Municipal Advisor (CIPMA) and holds a Series 50 Municipal Advisor Representative qualification.
Back to top 




 

Marvin L. Founds
Director, Columbus, OH


Contact Information 
(614) 987-1689 founds@umbaugh.com 



Formerly the Public Finance Managing Director of a large Midwest Capital Markets Investment Bank, Mr. Founds is now Umbaugh’s  Director of Ohio Education Finance providing municipal advisory services to schools and other local governments. Mr. Founds has been a public finance professional for more than 28 years serving as the Treasurer of a large Central Ohio School District prior to his experience as an investment banker.  Mr. Founds is a registered municipal advisor.
 
