Mark A. Miller
Director, Columbus, OH


Contact Information 
(614) 987-1684 mmiller@umbaugh.com 



Mark A. Miller is the Director of the Umbaugh Ohio office, providing assistance to local governments. His prior experience includes acting as managing director, and supervisory principal for a large Midwest Capital Markets Banking Group where he was responsible for marketing and executing capital markets solutions for public finance issuers. Mr. Miller has been a public finance professional for more than 25 years. He has served state treasurers, state agencies, counties, cities, colleges and universities, school districts, convention centers and airports.
Mark possesses a diverse professional background that includes positions in information systems development, internal audit, corporate trust, commercial lending, and investment banking. He received a Bachelor of Science Degree in Finance from The Pennsylvania State University, earned certifications as an EDP Auditor and Corporate Trust Specialist and graduated from Leadership Columbus. Over the years, he has developed and presented a variety of courses for the Ohio Treasurer of State’s Center for Public Investment Management (CPIM) Program, served as an adjunct professor at Bowling Green State University and has guest lectured at The Pennsylvania State University.
