Jesse Nelson serves as an independent financial advisor to Michigan school districts and local governmental units. He provides clients with options and recommendations that help them accomplish their capital improvement and financial goals.
Since joining Umbaugh in 2004, Nelson has assisted clients in a variety of ways, including completion of millage studies, capital improvement financial plans, School Bond Qualification and Loan Program (SBQLP) applications, bond issuance and utility rate and cost of service studies.
A graduate of Butler University’s College of Business Administration with a Bachelor of Science degree in accounting. Nelson is a Certified Public Accountant. He is a member of the Michigan Government Finance Officers Association, the Bond Club of Detroit and the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants.
Based in Umbaugh’s Lansing, Michigan office, Nelson has been the guest speaker on the topic of school improvement finance at regional and annual Michigan School Business Officials meetings. He has also served as an expert witness in the area of school finance.
