Deen C. Rogers, CPA
Partner, Indianapolis, IN


Contact Information 
(317) 465-1538 rogers@umbaugh.com 



Since joining Umbaugh in June 2000, Deen C. Rogers has been involved with numerous professional engagements including financial studies for municipally owned utilities, not-for-profit corporations, regional water and sewer districts and conservancy districts. These studies quite often have involved the determination of utility revenue requirements, cost-of-service studies and the financial planning associated with the issuance of tax-exempt bonds.  Deen is also the firm’s primary annexation expert, which has led to his involvement with dozens of clients in the preparation of over 100 fiscal plans.  Finally, Deen has also been responsible for the preparation of benefit-cost analyses for several TIGER grant applications. 
In 2013, Rogers became a Principal in the Accounting Services Group of Umbaugh.  A graduate of the Kelley School of Business at Indiana University in Bloomington, Indiana, with Bachelor of Science degrees in both Accounting and Finance, Rogers has also completed professional courses sponsored by the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants, the Indiana CPA Society, the Government Finance Officers Association and other professional organizations.
