Jeffrey P. Rowe, CPA
Partner, Mishawaka, IN


Contact Information 
(574) 935-5178 rowe@umbaugh.com 



Jeff Rowe provides accounting and financial advisory services for various governmental entities, and works primarily with public utilities.  Experience includes assisting municipalities with the issuance of tax-exempt securities for the financing of construction projects and the refinancing of outstanding debt. He also specializes in the area of rate-making for utilities requiring the development and restructuring of rates and charges for municipal water, sewer, stormwater and electric utilities, as well as regional water and sewer districts and conservancy districts.
Rowe also works with a number of communities to provide ongoing financial management services, including contract controllership services, the development of multi-year operating and capital improvement budgets, financial forecasting, maintenance of proper cash reserves, and guidance in the area of accounting and recording procedures.
Rowe is a 1997 graduate of Indiana University, South Bend, where he majored in accounting and earned a Bachelor of Science Degree in Business. He is a licensed Certified Public Accountant in the State of Indiana and is a member of the Indiana CPA Society, the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants, the Indiana Association for Floodplain and Stormwater Management and the American Water Works Association.  Rowe is also a licensed Municipal Financial Advisor.
