Paige E. Sansone, CPA
Partner, Indianapolis, IN


Contact Information 
(317) 465-1521 sansone@umbaugh.com 



Paige E. Sansone’s professional engagements include financial studies for municipalities that often determine the impact of levies, tax rates and assessed values based on changing local or legislative initiatives. In addition, she assists numerous taxing units with budget preparation and capital planning. She has been a guest speaker for many municipal and county events, such as the Newly Elected Official Training sponsored by AIM, the IMLCT Clerk’s Institute, and the County Commissioners Conference. She is also a featured instructor of the AIM-sponsored Municipal Management Institute.
Prior to joining Umbaugh in 2003, Sansone was the assistant budget director for the Indiana Department of Local Government Finance (DLGF). Her primary focus at DLGF was local government budgeting and she was a voting member of the Local Government Tax Control Board. Before working for the DLGF, Sansone was the administrative manager for the Seymour District of the Indiana Department of Transportation (INDOT).
Sansone is a graduate of Indiana University with a degree in finance and a Master of Professional Accountancy. Sansone lives in Indianapolis and is based in Umbaugh’s Indianapolis office.
