John M. Seever, CPA
Partner, Indianapolis, IN


Contact Information 
(317) 465-1507 seever@umbaugh.com 



John has been involved in many professional engagements, including financial studies for cities, towns and utilities. These studies often involve budgeting, financial reporting, annexation, consolidation and financial planning for municipalities and the determination of revenue requirements, cost-of-service studies and the financial planning associated with the issuance of debt and capital project planning for utilities.
He is a frequent speaker concerning municipal finance and utility rates before various trade groups including AIM, IMLA, IACC, IRWA and IWEA often serves as an expert witness on behalf of clients. John has testified before the Indiana General Assembly on matters related to utilities.
He is a member of the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants, the Indiana CPA Society and the Governmental Finance Officers Associations, among other professional groups. In addition, he currently serves on Accelerate Indiana Municipalities’ Board of Directors; he is past Chair of the Indiana Section American Water Works Association and was Chair of the AWWA National audit committee for two years.  John is a member of the Board of Directors of Easterseals Crossroads of Central Indiana.
Seever graduated from Indiana University – Bloomington. He joined Umbaugh in 1982 and is based in Indianapolis.
