Jason G. Semler, CPA
Partner, Indianapolis, IN


Contact Information 
(317) 465-1540 semler@umbaugh.com 



Jason G. Semler's practice includes economic development, financing and utility projects. His economic development work involves developing diverse revenue sources, such as tax increment financing (TIF) and local option income taxes, examining taxing units’ assessed values and their respective abatements, and the financial planning associated with the issuance of both tax-exempt and taxable bonds.
Semler has been involved in numerous governmental projects, including projects financed by bonds secured by ad valorem taxes, income taxes and food and beverage taxes. He also has assisted communities with their capital project planning efforts and analyzed the estimated impacts that recent and proposed property tax regulations could have on various clients throughout Indiana.
He is a member of the Indiana CPA Society and the Indiana Economic Development Association.
Jason is a graduate of Ball State University with a degree in finance with concentrations in corporate financial management and financial planning. He joined Umbaugh in 1999. A resident of Noblesville, Semler is based in the Indianapolis office.
