Tom Traciak
Principal, Lansing, MI


Contact Information 
(517) 321-0110 traciak@umbaugh.com 



Tom Traciak’s practice includes bond issues, grant funding, tax increment finance, rate studies and lease-purchase agreements for local governments throughout Michigan. He has a particular expertise in working with governments experiencing difficult credit and revenue support situations and has a concentration in water and sewer utilities.
Prior to joining Umbaugh in 2011, Traciak was president of ACI Finance, Inc. in Mason, Mich., a company he formed in 1996 that served local governments throughout Michigan with capital financings. He has worked in accounting, budgeting and finance in both the public and private sectors for more than 30 years.
Traciak is a graduate of the University of Michigan and earned his master’s degree in public policy and administration from Michigan State University.
Traciak is based in the Lansing Umbaugh office.
