(574) 935-5178 walsh@umbaugh.com 



Mr. Walsh is a graduate of Goshen College in Goshen, Indiana with a Bachelor of Arts degree with a major in Accounting.  He has also completed professional courses sponsored by the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants, the Indiana CPA Society, the American Water Works Association, the National Rural Electric Cooperative Association and other professional organizations.  Mr. Walsh is a member of the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants, the Indiana CPA Society and the American Water Works Association.  He has served as an expert witness before the Indiana Utility Regulatory Commission and local public hearings regarding utility rate making and tax exempt finance.  He also serves as on the board of directors for the Fulton County Rural Electric Membership Cooperative located in Rochester, IN.  Mr. Walsh has presented at seminars sponsored by the Accelerate Indiana Municipalities, the ILMCT Clerk’s Institute, the Alliance of Indiana Rural Water, and the Indiana Rural Water Association.
Eric joined Umbaugh in June 2006 and in 2008 successfully completed the requirements to become licensed as a Certified Public Accountant in the State of Indiana.  Eric has been involved with several professional engagements including budget services and financial studies for municipally-owned utilities, regional water and sewer districts and conservancy districts.  These studies quite often have involved the determination of utility revenue requirements, cost of service studies and the financial planning associated with the issuance of tax-exempt bonds.
Eric focuses his efforts on Financial Management Services in response to client needs ranging from training, budget services, annual reporting, financial management reports, tax exempt bond issuance, cost of service studies and advanced services involving financial accounting and reporting.
